node.text: Meet Lilian Liu, a strategist who's building better societies through sustainable business. Lilian works with Futerra, an agency that helps companies put Earth first, and engages people while doing it. She's also worked with the United Nations, Fashion Act Now, and is a Greenbiz 30 Under 30 honoree. Get to know @lilianliu at the link up top.

node.title: Getting Stuff Done with Lilian Liu

node.text: We are super proud to be partnering with The City of Los Angeles and @MayorofLA Eric Garcetti on LA Protects, an initiative to organize local manufacturers to make 5 million non-medical masks. We will also work with our in-house teams to make these masks in the Reformation Factory, using fabrics from our warehouse. Visit laprotects.org for more info.

node.text: It comes as no surprise that New Year’s Eve is the most overrated night of the year. But you might still go out and endure the whole thing. Or maybe you’ll stay in and get dressed up because we all know that’s the only part that’s actually super fun.

node.title: My New Year’s Eve is Better Than Yours

node.text: We love introducing you guys to super cool women doing really impressive things who also happen to wear Ref. So for our new Holiday Collection, we decided to hang out with four of our favorites who are impacting the world big time in their own way. Check out the landing page to learn more about Devaki Raj, Sarah Paiji Yoo, Grace Mahary, and Ellie Dinh.
